USAGE
-----
Usage: python peakzilla.py [OPTIONS] chip.bed control.bed > results.tsv

Options:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  -s FRAGMENT_SIZE, --fragment_size=FRAGMENT_SIZE
                        upper limit of fragment size in bp: default=200
  -f FDR, --fdr=FDR     cutoff for the estimated FDR value: default = 1
  -c SCORE_CUTOFF, --score_cutoff=SCORE_CUTOFF
                        minimum cutoff for score (~ fold enrichment): default
                        = 2
  -q, --quiet           don't print status messages


DEPENDENCIES
------------
* Runs on OSX and Linux based operating systems.
* Requires Python 2.5 or greater
* For up to 5x better perormance use PyPy instead of CPython


INPUT FORMAT
------------
Peakzilla accepts BED formated alignments as input.

For converstion to BED format and working with BED files and alignments in
general I highly reccommend:

* bowtie (http://bowtie-bio.sourceforge.net/)
* SAMtools (http://samtools.sourceforge.net/)
* bedtools (http://code.google.com/p/bedtools/)


WORKFLOW EXAMPLE
----------------
# use bowtie to map uniquely mappable reads to the genome
bowtie -p4 -m1 --sam genome_index input.fastq input.sam
bowtie -p4 -m1 --sam genome_index chip.fastq chip.sam

# convert to BAM format
samtools view -bS input.sam > input.bam
samtools view -bS chip.sam > chip.bam

# convert to BED format
bamToBed -i input.bam > input.bed
bamToBed -i chip.bam > chip.bed

# run peakzilla
python peakzilla.py chip.bed input.bed > chip_results.tsv


OPTIONS
-------
One of peakzilla's design goals is to learn all the necessary information
from the data. The usage of the options should therefore not be required.

FRAGMENT_SIZE
How large or small the fragment size will be modeled is loosely constrained
by this parameter. As most protocols for ChIP sequencing involve selecting
fragments of around 200 bp it is set to 200.

FDR
Cutoff for accepted false discovery rate, as estimated from the control
sample.

SCORE_CUTOFF
Minnimum fold enrichment over background required for the peak to be
printed to output.


OUTPUT FORMAT
-------------
* Results are printed as a table of tab delimited values to stdout.
* Status messages are printed to stderr. 

